 {"id":"bd-mzct","title":"Add unit tests for Ext4Superblock query methods in ffs-ondisk","description":"The ffs-ondisk ext4.rs module has 206 tests but several Ext4Superblock query methods are tested only through the ffs-ext4 facade. Add direct unit tests in ffs-ondisk/src/ext4.rs for: parse_from_image, has_compat/has_incompat/has_ro_compat, is_64bit, group_desc_size, groups_count, has_metadata_csum, csum_seed, validate_checksum, validate_geometry, validate_v1, feature_diagnostics_v1, group_desc_offset, inode_table_offset, locate_inode, inode_device_offset. These tests complement the facade tests already added in ffs-ext4.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-26T03:23:28.818125035Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-26T03:35:03.599721597Z","closed_at":"2026-02-26T03:35:03.599691791Z","close_reason":"Added 25 unit tests for Ext4Superblock query methods in ffs-ondisk/src/ext4.rs: has_compat, has_incompat, has_ro_compat, is_64bit, group_desc_size, groups_count, has_metadata_csum, csum_seed, validate_checksum, group_desc_offset, inode_table_offset, parse_from_image. All 293 tests pass, clippy clean, fmt clean.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ondisk","quality","tests"]}
 {"id":"bd-n3s3","title":"ffs-cli fails to compile due to missing ioctl_trace_path field","description":"In crates/ffs-cli/src/main.rs, MountOptions is initialized without the recently added ioctl_trace_path field, causing E0063 compilation errors.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-18T16:50:51.015872536Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-18T17:17:04.588931935Z","closed_at":"2026-04-18T17:17:04.586214758Z","close_reason":"Verified: ffs-cli MountOptions initializers include ioctl_trace_path; rch cargo check -p ffs-cli passes","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-n5l9","title":"Align ffs-core durability autopilot floor with ffs-repair policy","description":"ffs-core::DurabilityAutopilot currently accepts/chooses 1% repair overhead (1.01 multiplier), but ffs-repair::autopilot defaults to a 3%-10% search range. This cross-crate drift lets the public RepairPolicy surface undercut the actual repair policy floor. Raise the ffs-core autopilot minimum candidate/default range to 3%-10%, update public docs/comments, and adjust facade/core tests accordingly. Acceptance: ffs-core/ffs tests reflect [1.03, 1.10] bounds and targeted rch check/test pass.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:38:13.252142493Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-01T20:45:28.388823859Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T20:45:28.388554659Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"bd-n8blq","title":"Conformance harness: build syscall-level conformance tests vs reference fs","description":"Apply /testing-conformance-harnesses skill. Build a conformance test that drives our fs through the same syscall sequences as a reference (Linux ext4 in tmpfs). Differential diff outputs per syscall (return value, errno, side effects). Cover: file lifecycle, directory ops, attribute ops, link semantics, mmap interaction, fsync semantics, mount/umount.","notes":"Extended the existing syscall-level differential harness with two recent coverage slices. Commit 6dc719f added offset I/O coverage: pread/pwrite, SEEK_END, fdatasync fallback behavior, final file bytes/size/link mode metadata, alongside existing lifecycle/dir/link/mmap/fsync steps. Commit 47b5bf6 added utime/access/openat/statvfs coverage: frozen atime/mtime mutation, R_OK/W_OK/X_OK checks, directory-relative open via dir_fd with deterministic fallback, and normalized statvfs invariants. Fresh-eyes cleanup hardening tolerates the Python offset-I/O skip path without unlinking a missing io.bin; it also makes the dir_fd capability check tolerate older Python runtimes without os.supports_dir_fd and aligns the scenario result wording with the statvfs probe. Validation for code commit 47b5bf6 with bead metadata commit c716521 on top: targeted fuse_conformance_syscall_sequence_matches_linux_reference passed with worker FUSE mount soft-skip after reference probe; cargo fmt --check passed; UBS touched files passed with 0 critical and existing warning inventory; workspace cargo check --workspace --all-targets passed; workspace cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings passed; parity_report_matches_feature_parity_md passed; full cargo test -p ffs-harness -- --nocapture passed; cargo bench -p ffs-harness exited 0. Criterion flagged parser microbenchmark regressions, but this slice changed only the FUSE harness script and FEATURE_PARITY.md. Agent Mail remained red, so no reservation/release.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-fs","created_at":"2026-04-24T22:22:37.099317207Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T16:04:22.209096193Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-n8blq","title":"Conformance harness: build syscall-level conformance tests vs reference fs","description":"Apply /testing-conformance-harnesses skill. Build a conformance test that drives our fs through the same syscall sequences as a reference (Linux ext4 in tmpfs). Differential diff outputs per syscall (return value, errno, side effects). Cover: file lifecycle, directory ops, attribute ops, link semantics, mmap interaction, fsync semantics, mount/umount.","notes":"Extended the existing syscall-level differential harness with two recent coverage slices. Commit 6dc719f added offset I/O coverage: pread/pwrite, SEEK_END, fdatasync fallback behavior, final file bytes/size/link mode metadata, alongside existing lifecycle/dir/link/mmap/fsync steps. Commit 47b5bf6 added utime/access/openat/statvfs coverage: frozen atime/mtime mutation, R_OK/W_OK/X_OK checks, directory-relative open via dir_fd with deterministic fallback, and normalized statvfs invariants. Fresh-eyes cleanup hardening tolerates the Python offset-I/O skip path without unlinking a missing io.bin; it also makes the dir_fd capability check tolerate older Python runtimes without os.supports_dir_fd and aligns the scenario result wording with the statvfs probe. Metadata cleanup corrected the validation note so it no longer calls code commit 47b5bf6 current HEAD after the c716521 bead metadata commit landed. Fresh-eyes validation for this cleanup: cargo fmt --check passed; git diff --check passed; UBS touched files passed with 0 critical findings and only existing warning inventory in fuse_e2e.rs; rch cargo test -p ffs-harness --test fuse_e2e fuse_conformance_syscall_sequence_matches_linux_reference -- --nocapture passed with worker FUSE mount soft-skip after reference probe; rch cargo test -p ffs-harness parity_report_matches_feature_parity_md -- --nocapture passed; rch cargo check --workspace --all-targets passed; rch cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings passed. Prior validation for code commit 47b5bf6 with c716521 bead metadata on top also included full cargo test -p ffs-harness -- --nocapture and cargo bench -p ffs-harness exiting 0, with Criterion reporting parser microbenchmark regressions unrelated to the FUSE harness/docs slice. Agent Mail remained red, so no reservation/release.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-fs","created_at":"2026-04-24T22:22:37.099317207Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T16:09:22.532177803Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
